E. COLI EHEC - AUSTRALIA (06): (QUEENSLAND) PETTING ZOO, O157
*************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 5 Sep 2013
Source: The Australian [edited]
http://www.theaustralian.com.au/news/breaking-news/ekka-e-coli-infections-rise-to-40/story-fn3dxiwe-1226711578179


There are now 40 confirmed cases of _E. coli_ infection. Of these, 27 are children aged between 1-15. The oldest person infected is 77.

Authorities say EHEC genes that code for the toxin were detected in the bedding of animals in the Ekka's pet area. A Queensland Health spokesman said the number of cases are likely to increase as authorities wait for further samples to be tested.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The Queensland Health Facebook page on 6 Sep 2013 (https://www.facebook.com/QLDHealth) updated the overall confirmed number cases to 44 but did not specify how many additional suspected cases have yet to be confirmed or whether some of the suspected cases had been ruled out. - Mod.LL.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1z_*.]
